On March 12, the wife of Canadian Prime Minister Trudo was diagnosed with the new coronavirus.

TRUDO's wife, Sophy, who has mild symptoms but is in stable condition, will be put into isolation immediately, according to a statement released by his office that day.

Trudo will also begin a 14 day self imposed quarantine as a precautionary measure, the statement said. But as he has not developed any symptoms, the doctor advised him not to have a new coronavirus test. The doctor also said there was no risk to people who had been in contact with Trudeau in the recent past.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Trudeau's office says. Source: Global BC

The new crown pneumonia epidemic continues to spread at an alarming rate across North America. As of press time, new coronavirus infections have been detected in seven Canadian provinces, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 150 and one death.

In order to prevent further deterioration of the epidemic, some Canadian provinces announced the cancellation and restrictions on large-scale activities. British Columbia, Richmond and Alberta，Prov.of have all decided to ban group activities for more than 250 people, and Montreal, Richmond's largest city, has closed all swimming pools, skating rinks and libraries, ontario announced that public schools across the province would be closed from March 14 until April 5.

Canada's neighbor, the United States, is also facing a major challenge from the new pneumonia outbreak. On 12 March, the first confirmed case of new coronavirus emerged at United Nations headquarters in New York.

A female Philippine diplomat at the United Nations was diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia on Thursday, Reuters reported. "starting today, the Philippine mission to the United Nations will be immediately closed, all personnel will be quarantined and will seek medical attention if symptoms develop, " said the Philippines' Acting Ambassador to the United Nations, Kira Azucena. At this point, we assume everyone is infected."

According to the United Nations Diplomatic Staff Online directory, the Philippine mission is located on Fifth Avenue in Manhattan and has about 12 diplomats.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The mayor of New York City, best buy, at the cheese shop on March 10. Source: twitter

New York City declared a state of emergency on Thursday amid concerns about the outbreak. Mayor Bill De Blasio told a news conference that there were 95 new cases of the virus in New York City, but that number is expected to rise sharply next week. Twenty-nine people in New York City are in mandatory quarantine, and 1,784 are in voluntary quarantine.

He said the mayor has the power to impose curfews, close roads and bridges, stop public transport and impose food rationing during a state of emergency. He also stressed that the above measures are just examples and are not yet in place.

Bill de Blasio also said the fight against the outbreak could last as long as six months. New York City will eventually be able to overcome the epidemic, but it will have to keep its public schools, public transport and, most importantly, its health system running. He said the city government would do "whatever it takes" to make sure the three systems were working properly. Bill de Blasio also said authorities were studying the feasibility of converting a municipal car park into a makeshift hospital.

As of press time, more than 1,600 new cases of pneumonia have been confirmed in the United States, and more than 40 people have died, according to several organizations.
